{"body": "FWIW, back when I wrote MetaWhere, inspired by a quick hack of a gist that @lifo showed me, some folks made a case to merge it (or something like it) into core. It was turned down for a few pretty good reasons, one of them being the extensions to Symbol being considered poor form. I could be remembering wrong, but I seem to recall @dkubb saying that datamapper 2.0 was moving away from Symbol extensions as well. So it would seem that this would be heading in the wrong direction. ", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/5296374", "created_at": "2012-04-24T02:27:06Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/5948#issuecomment-5296374", "updated_at": "2012-04-24T02:27:06Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 5948, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ernie/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ernie/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ernie/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/ernie", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ernie/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/ernie", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ernie/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://2.gravatar.com/avatar/2274a7476f6d2ac7aedcdec0651d0542?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F6a600c968f4e6a843dcaf600c1694e42.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ernie/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ernie/received_events", "gravatar_id": "2274a7476f6d2ac7aedcdec0651d0542", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ernie/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "ernie", "type": "User", "id": 14947, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ernie/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "52381101bd3543c15100d743"}, "id": 5296374, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/5948"}
